    "name": "FEA acceptance bounds for ASTM F1717 compression-bending QoIs",
    "description": "The FEA modeling framework shall predict construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement within 10% of the experimental mean for each QoI, and the normalized model error E/uval shall be less than 1.96 for all three QoIs. This requirement is derived from FDA guidance on computational modeling credibility and the pre-specified statistical acceptance plan documented in the test protocol.",
    "source": "FDA Guidance on Assessing the Credibility of Computational Modeling and Simulation, 2023; ASTM F1717-21"
